LOGIN:

- The first thing a user should see is the “Login page” where the user must be able to enter their name.
- Remember to first check if the user exists.

  A. If exists:
  B. Create new user and send to
  --> Send to Translation Page (Main page)

  TRANSLATION:

- You may choose to limit the input to 40 letters. (Not required)
- The user must click on the “translate” button to the right of the input box to trigger the translation.
- You may ignore special characters and spaces.

  PROFILE:

- Display translations from local db.json (Max 10)
- must display the last 10 translations for the current user
- You only need to display the text of the translation
- There must also be a button to clear the translations. This should “delete” in your API and no longer display
  on the profile page.
- Delete from local when delete button!
- The Logout button should clear all the storage and return to the start page

